commText: That's it for tonight. We will be back tomorrow. See you then. Bye.

Riyan Parag | Player of the Match: [emotions] They are settled, mom is here, she has seen the struggle, the last 3-4 years. I know what my opinion is about myself. That does not change regardless of whether I get a zero or not. That's a lot to do with the type of season as well, I had a great domestic season and that helps. Someone in the top four has to play the 20 overs, the wicket was keeping low and stopping, in the first game Sanju bhayya did it. I have worked very hard, the last 3 days I was in bed, I was on painkillers, I just got up today and I'm very happy.

Sanju Samson | RR captain: It was a bit of a roller-coaster. The way we started the first 10 overs, OK, Rovman get ready you may have to bat today. But the way the batters took the responsibility it was fantastic. Absolutely he did. The game is changing and we all have to be flexible. It was earlier about 11 players, now it's about 15 players. Sanga and I had 4-5 chats around the 13th-17th over. But what Riyan did in that 20th over made it easy. It is all about gauging in which zone they are, you have to look at that and take the decision accordingly. Sandy was calm and Avesh as well and I took that call. Riyan has been a big name for the last 3-4 years, everywhere I go, in Kerala they ask me, when is he going to come good? touchwood, this is the season. He has to keep his head down and has a lot to give to Indian cricket.

Stats round-up by Shashikant Singh * Last season RR lost four out of five home games at Jaipur. They already won 2 out of 2 this season. Most sixes in an IPL game in Jaipur 24 - RR vs SRH, 2023 19 - RR vs LSG, 2024 17 - RR vs DC, today* 14 - RR vs PBKS, 2008 DC innings progression Overs 1-6: 59/2 (RR: 9.83) Overs 7-10: 30/0 (RR: 7.50) Overs 11-15: 31/2 (RR: 5.20) Overs 16-20: 53/1 (RR: 10.60) Pace vs spin in DC innings Spin: 2/49 in 6 overs (ER 8.16) Pace: 3/123 in 14 overs (ER 8.78)

Avesh Khan - My plan was clear, one side was longer and I wanted to bowl wide yorkers. I gave myself 5 seconds every ball to think and then execute the plan. If the batters play a good shot, it's good for him, but I always back my yorkers. We have Boult, Burger and Sandy, I've learnt a lot from them. The team management and Kumar Sangakkara have supported us a lot and have made us not worry too much about the fear of failure. I always want to improve, I want to invent new types of deliveries in T20s. I rest and relax well, work hard in the nets and that has allowed me improve my skills.

Rishabh Pant | DC captain: Definitely disappointed. Best thing we can do from this is learn from it. The bowlers did really well till 15-16 overs, batters sometimes go on at the death and score quickly, that happened in this game. Marsh and Warner gave a good start, but we lost a few wickets in the middle overs and in the end we had too many runs to cover up. There are other options, we wanted Nortje to bowl at the death and sometimes you can go for runs, hopefully we can do better in the next match.

23:25 Local Time, 17:55 GMT, 23:25 IST: I0$. The trend continues. Earlier, Marsh and Warner got off to a fast start before the former was bowled by Burger who took Bhui as well in the same over. Pant and Warner strung a stand after that but the pace was slow. Warner fell for 49 and Pant soon after. The Impact Player Porel did not contribute much and even though Tristan Stubbs tried some late heroics, Sandeep Sharma and Avesh Khan kept their nerves to take RR home. The wicket got slower as the game went on and RR were well-led by Samson who handled his bowling changes nicely. Two each for Burger and Chahal and fine death bowling from Sandeep and Avesh. Stay tuned for the presentation...
Avesh Khan to Axar, 1 run, RR win. Full on the stumps, clipped to deep mid-wicket and only one
Avesh Khan to Axar, no run, a low full-toss outside off, Axar drives and misses
Avesh Khan to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, celebrations in the RR camp. Was in the slot outside off, Tristan Stubbs though inside-edges the loft to backward square leg and it's just one
15 off 3. Just needs one good ball and the game is done. Buttler has a word with Avesh Khan.
Avesh Khan to Axar, 1 run, this is fine death bowling. Very full and just outside off, driven to long-off
Avesh Khan to Axar, no run, fine yorker length delivery outside off, Axar can't run it down to third man
Avesh Khan to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, fine yorker length delivery outside off, dug out to extra-cover
17 off the last over. Who will bowl? Either Burger or Boult. Even Avesh is an option. And Avesh it is.
Sandeep Sharma to Axar, 2 runs, wide yorker length delivery outside off, squeezed out to deep backward point and Burger gets across and cuts it off with a slide
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, wide yorker length delivery outside off, Tristan Stubbs drags it to backward square leg off a thick inside-edge
Sandeep Sharma to Axar, 1 run, low full-toss angling into off-stump, lofted on the bounce to long-on
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, full and wide outside off, driven to long-off
Immediately Samson goes to Sandeep Sharma to have a word.
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, mauled wide of extra-cover. A wide length delivery outside off, Tristan Stubbs uses all his strength to cut that into the gap

Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, what power. A slower short delivery outside off, immense power from Tristan Stubbs as he gets forward and flat-bats it over wide long-on, Parag was in with a chance, but it went over his head
Sandeep Sharma [3.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Avesh Khan to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, half-volley outside off, driven hard and wide of extra-cover and Burger again does well to stop it
Avesh Khan to Axar, 1 run, a low full-toss on off, driven hard and straight to long-off
Avesh Khan to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, wide yorker outside off, Tristan Stubbs premeditates the reverse-sweep and toe-ends it wide of cover
Avesh Khan to Axar, 1 run, slower ball wide outside off, cut hard to extra-cover, Burger fumbles a little, throws it to Avesh Khan who deflects it on to the stumps, Axar is in comfortably
Avesh Khan to Axar, wide, this is wide of the tramline on the off-side, lands past the popping crease
Avesh Khan to Axar, no run, wide yorker length delivery outside off, Axar fails to make any contact, looks for a wide but it's inside the line
Avesh Khan to Axar, FOUR, nice. Full outside off, width was there, Axar opens the face of the bat and runs it down wide of short third man
Avesh Khan [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Ashwin to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, six more. Full carrom ball outside off, Tristan Stubbs lofts clean and over wide long-on. Ends the over well, 19 off it

Ashwin to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, next ball goes for six. A flat carrom ball on the stumps, on a length, Tristan Stubbs pulls it hard and over deep mid-wicket, Boult is in a few paces from the cushions and can only watch it sail over, wouldn't have mattered anyway
Abishek Porel vs Chahal in IPL 8 balls 5 runs two dismissals

Ashwin to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, Boult makes a meal of that at deep mid-wicket. Full carrom ball on the stumps, Tristan Stubbs on the slogsweep top-edges it, Boult comes in and strangely stutters and stops, he puts his left hand up at the last moment, it flicks the hand and goes down
Ashwin to Axar, 1 run, full outside off, swept in the air but in front of deep mid-wicket running in
Ashwin to Axar, wide, fired wide outside off and wide of the tramline
Ashwin to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, carrom ball on a back of a length on off, pulled to deep square leg
Ashwin to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, carrom ball on a good length on the stumps, swiped wide of deep mid-wicket for two
Ravichandran Ashwin [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (12-16 overs) - Warner falls for 49, Avesh breaks the partnership - Sandeep Sharma bowls a couple of tidy oivers - Chahal gets the big wicket of Pant - Chahal picks up a second as Porel holes out
Chahal to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, full on the stumps, driven to long-off
Chahal to Axar, 1 run, again that wide length delivery outside off, cut to deep backward point
Chahal to Axar, 2 runs, flat good length outside off, cut wide of cover-point and wide of deep backward point too, Axar starts with two
Axar Patel, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Chahal to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Buttler!! Abishek Porel holes out. He gives the charge and lofts but it's not off the middle, straight to long-off and Buttler won't drop those. It's the timeout as well. RR favorites from here. Abishek Porel c Buttler b Chahal 9(10)
Chahal to Abishek Porel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Chahal to Abishek Porel, no run, again Abishek Porel comes down the track and this time he finds cover-point, no chance of a single
Chahal to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, Abishek Porel comes down the track and it's wider outside off, he toe-ends the loft and it's wide of extra-cover for two
Sandeep Sharma to Abishek Porel, 1 run, another slower ball which is short outside off, dabbed to short third man for one
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, slower and dug in short outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket
Sandeep Sharma to Abishek Porel, 1 run, slower ball wide outside off, Abishek Porel cuts to deep backward point
Sandeep Sharma to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, slower ball on a good length outside off, dabbed wide of Ashwin at short third man, he dives and parries it, they come back for two
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, slower ball on a back of a length outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, fine shot. A wide slower ball on a back of a length outside off, Tristan Stubbs punches hard and wide of the diving Jaiswal at extra-cover
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, wide, way outside off, Tristan Stubbs shuffles across and tries to sweep, misses, called a wide
Chahal to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, tossed up full outside off, driven wide of long-off and an easy two
Chahal to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, tossed up on leg-stump, Tristan Stubbs gets forward to drive to long-on
Chahal to Abishek Porel, 1 run, Abishek Porel comes down the track and pushes the wide delivery wide of extra-cover for one
Chahal to Abishek Porel, no run, another slider outside off, similar to Pant's dismissal, Abishek Porel tries to run it down, misses, Samson fumbles too and there was no edge
Chahal to Abishek Porel, no run, back of a length on off, Abishek Porel makes room to punch to extra-cover
Abishek Porel, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Chahal to Pant, out Caught by Samson!! Pant walks. Wide length delivery outside off, Pant looks to cut and edges it. Clear deflection and gone. DC slip. Pant is not happy, while going inside the dressing room, he hits the fluffy cushions with his bat. Pant c Samson b Chahal 28(26) [4s-2 6s-1]
Chahal to Pant, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Yuzvendra Chahal [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack

Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, no run, again it's Jaiswal, and again a batter is halfway down, but this time Jaiswal fumbles, the chance goes, Tristan Stubbs gets forward and drives to extra-cover and sets off
Sandeep Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower ball fullish outside off, Pant kneels low and swats it to deep mid-wicket
Sandeep Sharma to Pant, wide, the seam-up full delivery outside off, but too wide and wide called
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, fuller and wider outside off, Tristan Stubbs shuffles across and drives to sweeper cover
Sandeep Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, slashed to deep backward point
Sandeep Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, full outside off, Tristan Stubbs shuffles across and drives to sweeper cover
Sandeep Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to deep backward point
Warner vs Avesh Khan in IPL 17 balls 20 runs 2 dismissals 117.64 SR 10 dots
Avesh Khan to Tristan Stubbs, no run, right through Tristan Stubbs. A short of length delivery and nips back in, beats the defence and goes over the inside-edge and the stumps
Avesh Khan to Pant, 1 run, fullish outside off, Pant reaches for it and mistimes the drive to cover for one
Avesh Khan to Pant, no run, full outside off, driven nicely but straight to the fielder at extra-cover
Avesh Khan to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, short of length on off, defended to mid-on for one
Tristan Stubbs, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Avesh Khan to Warner, out Caught by Sandeep Sharma!! Good catch and Warner goes. Full and wide outside off, he reaches for it to drive, thick outside-edge and Sandeep at short third man dives to his right to take it with both hands. They check for a clean catch and it is. Warner is not even waiting, he is walking off. Warner c Sandeep Sharma b Avesh Khan 49(34) [4s-5 6s-3]
Avesh Khan to Warner, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Avesh Khan to Warner, FOUR, slower good length outside off, Warner swats it to the deep square leg fence, no-one there, all along the ground too
Avesh Khan [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (7-11 overs) - Avesh greeted with a back to back fours from Warner - Jaiswal and Ashwin fluff a run-out chance, Warner survives - Warner and Pant bring up the 50-run stand - Jurel palms over a tough chance off Pant over the rope
Sandeep Sharma to Warner, 1 run, slower ball on a length outside off, Warner walks and bunts it to long-off
Sandeep Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower ball wide on a length outside off, Pant reaches for it to cut to deep backward point
Sandeep Sharma to Warner, 1 run, full seam-up outside off, lofted wide of long-off
Sandeep Sharma to Warner, no run, slower ball fullish outside off, Warner reaches for it to cut and mistimes it to cover
Sandeep Sharma to Warner, no run, slower ball dug in outside off, Warner pulls and misses, wanted to hit it too hard
Sandeep Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Pant slashes to sweeper cover
Sandeep Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Chahal to Pant, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Pant drags the sweep to deep backward square leg
Chahal to Pant, no run, fullish outside off, driven straight to the fielder at cover-point

Chahal to Pant, SIX, palmed over. Jurel the man. It's tossed up full outside off, Pant slogsweeps and it was a catching chance, Jurel went to his right, hit the end of his hands and what's worse, it went over the cushions at deep mid-wicket, immediately Chahal looks at Samson after that goes for six
Chahal to Warner, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Warner gets forward to drive to long-off
Chahal to Warner, no run, pushed through outside off, slider from the front of the hand, keeps very low, Warner pulls and misses, Chahal has a wry smile at Warner
Chahal to Pant, 1 run, angles it across Pant, fraction short outside off, cut to deep backward point
Yuzvendra Chahal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Ashwin to Pant, 1 run, Pant threatens to shimmy down, then the length is short, so he rocks back and pulls to deep backward square leg
Ashwin to Warner, 1 run, drifting in on a good length on leg-stump, Warner punches to long-on
Ashwin to Pant, 1 run, tossed up full on off, Pant gets forward to push to long-on
Ashwin to Pant, FOUR, flat fast and quick outside off, Pant goes on the back foot and cuts wide of backward point, used the depth of the crease so well
Ashwin to Pant, no run, slower and wider outside off, Pant mistimes the drive to extra-cover

Ashwin to Pant, no run, what a let-off for Warner. Total confusion between Pant and Warner, Pant pushes to cover, Warner is halfway down, no way back for him, Jaiswal throws it hard on the bounce to Ashwin who can't collect, allows Warner to get back. Ashwin has a go at Jaiswal for that throw, will that be the turning point?
Avesh Khan to Warner, no run, short of length outside off, Warner lets out a grunt of frustration as he mistimes the cut to cover
Avesh Khan round the wicket. No scratch that, he stays over the wicket.
Avesh Khan to Warner, no run, yorker length outside off, jammed out towards cover
Avesh Khan to Pant, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Pant gets forward to punch to sweeper cover
Avesh Khan to Warner, 1 run, short of length outside off, cut to sweeper cover

Avesh Khan to Warner, FOUR, slower short of length delivery on the stumps, Warner half-pulls, almost mindful of the fielder at deep backward square leg, but he gets it wide of that man, one bounce over the ropes
Avesh Khan to Warner, FOUR, was a wide had Warner left that. Instead he reaches and gets bat on that, drives it wide of backward point and the diving Chahal at sweeper cover
Avesh Khan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Samson is conversing to Ashwin in Tamil, as he often does.
Ashwin to Warner, 1 run, flat back of a length on middle, Warner makes room and punches to sweeper cover
Ashwin to Pant, 1 run, full and Pant comes down the track to push it to long-on
Ashwin to Warner, 1 run, "odunga na" [run anna], shouts Samson to Ashwin in Tamil as Warner mistimes the drive to Ashwin's left, but the single is taken
Ashwin to Warner, no run, tossed up full on off, Warner mistimes the drive to cover again
Ashwin to Warner, no run, fullish just outside off, Warner leans back and mistimes the drive to cover
Ashwin to Pant, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, slogsweep to deep mid-wicket
Ravichandran Ashwin, right-arm off break, comes into the attack

Highlights (1-6 overs) - No wicket in Boult's first over - Marsh smashes Burger for three fours - Boult taken for 13 runs in his 2nd over - Burger knocks over Marsh - Rajasthan waste a review for LBW against Bhui - Burger bounces out Bhui in the same over - Pant off the mark with a four - Warner v Boult - 6, 0, 0, 6, 1 - in the 5th over - Warner feasts on Burger, smashes a four and six
Timeout! DC have had a good powerplay despite losing two wickets. Still a long way to go though.
Nandre Burger to Pant, 1 run, good length on the stumps, turned through the vacant mid-wicket area
Nandre Burger to Pant, no run, rising short of length delivery outside off, extra bounce and Pant is lucky not to edge that as he plays and misses
Nandre Burger to Pant, no run, full and sliding down leg, Pant flicks and misses, off the pad to mid-wicket
Nandre Burger to Warner, leg byes, 1 run, full and down leg, Warner flicks and misses, off the pad
Nandre Burger to Warner, SIX, back of a length and coming into the tummy, Warner crouches a bit and pulls it over backward square leg, flies all the way, now Nandre Burger under pressure
Nandre Burger to Warner, FOUR, so so close. Fullish around off, Warner stays leg-side and pushes at it, thick inside-edge and it misses the stumps, runs away to the fine-leg fence
Boult to Pant, no run, good length just outside off, Pant is early into the punch, hits it in the air, but well short of mid-off
Boult to Warner, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to Parag at backward point and he fumbles, sloppy
Boult to Warner, SIX, no swing and straight through the line, full on the stumps, half-volley and Warner lofts with a full face straight down the ground
Boult to Warner, no run, slower ball on a good length on off, patted to backward point again
Boult to Warner, no run, short of length outside off, tapped to backward point who dives to his right and stops it, Parag it is
Boult to Warner, SIX, fine shot. Pre-meditated but Warner pulls it off, goes low and takes the length ball and scoops it all the way over short fine-leg

Nandre Burger to Pant, no run, back of a length and nips back in on the stumps, Pant is late on the defence, rapped on the pads but a bit too high and the appeal for LBW is turned down. Superb over nonetheless
Nandre Burger to Pant, FOUR, 147.8kph, but Pant has played that well, fullish outside off, guided with an open face wide of backward point and runs away for four
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Nandre Burger to Bhui, out Caught by Samson!! Does not matter the last ball. This fellow is special. One to watch out for in the future. Sheer pace. A throat-threatening short ball and Bhui is like a cat on a hot tin roof - does not know what to do, gloves it and a simple catch to Samson. Failures in both games for Bhui and RR fight back. Bhui c Samson b Nandre Burger 0(2)
Nandre Burger to Bhui, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Nandre Burger to Bhui, no run, RR lose a review. It was plumb as the pace on that beat the defence, but it has pitched outside the leg-stump, there ends the story
Ricky Bhui, right handed bat, comes to the crease
DRS! Samson takes a review for an LBW. No bat. Pitching outside the leg-stump.

Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, out Bowled!! Knocked him over. That's pacy and beats the defence of Mitchell Marsh. A short of length delivery on off, sheer pace and goes past the angled bat of Marsh, the off-stump is pegged back. The dangerous opening stand is broken. Mitchell Marsh b Nandre Burger 23(12) [4s-5]
Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Nandre Burger to Warner, 1 run, short of length just outside off, Warner punches square of the wicket on the off-side for one
Boult to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, fullish and angling into off-stump, slightly slower too, Mitchell Marsh gets forward and lofts with a high elbow, over mid-on and four more
Boult to Mitchell Marsh, no run, short of length and tight on off, Mitchell Marsh goes on the back foot to defend to cover
Boult to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, floaty full knuckle-ball outside off, Mitchell Marsh gets forward and thumps the drive wide of cover, clean and races away
Boult to Warner, 1 run, slower good length on the stumps, turned to deep backward square leg
Boult to Warner, FOUR, short of length on the stumps, fraction short and Warner is quick to latch on, pulls over mid-wicket, not off the middle but will do
Boult to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, from round the wicket, short of length on the stumps, nips back in and Mitchell Marsh gets a thick inside-edge on the defence to the mid-wicket area

Coming back to that opening over chaos - there were 3 foreigners on the field, and suddenly Ponting raised an issue and on came Powell and out went an Indian fielder. So now four foreigners are on the field. RR swapped a foreigner for a foreigner when they got Burger for Hetmyer.
Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, short of length just outside off, Mitchell Marsh dabs it with an open face to deep backward point
Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, no run, short of length and tight on the stumps, defended

Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, now the ball flies wide of short third man. Full outside off, Mitchell Marsh drives and the thick outside-edge just flies, Boult just moved and then gaved up to his left, he had no chance again

Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, straight through the line, full on off, Mitchell Marsh gets forward and lofts the drive, mid-off is slightly wide and he has no chance, even on the full-length dive to his right
Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, no run, full on the stumps, pushed to mid-off
A wide slip in.
Nandre Burger to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, a half-volley to start outside off, Mitchell Marsh gets forward to lace the drive wide of cover, just a stride forward and put it away
Nandre Burger, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Boult to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, full on the pads, flicked to deep square leg

Now the fourth umpire takes a sheet of paper and goes to Ponting to make his case. Remember RR only played 3 foreign players, so they can make an Impact Sub as their fourth foreigner. Hopefully Ponting and DC understand that rule.
Boult to Warner, 1 run, Warner is away, fullish on the stumps, nudged in front of mid-on for one
Boult to Warner, no run, short of length on off, defended to cover
Boult to Warner, no run, good length on off, Warner taps to the right of Powell who dives to his right and saves runs, immediate impact from Powell

Again a break in play. Not sure what the issue is. Nitin Menon goes to Warner and says something. Buttler comes to Menon to have a chat. Ponting is having an animated chat with the fourth umpire. And all of a sudden Rovman Powell comes in to field and an Indian player goes off the field. Ponting is very angry. Not sure why. So much chaos and so little clarity.
Boult to Warner, no run, good length and on middle, Warner goes on the back foot to defend to mid-on
Boult to Warner, no run, swing to start for Boult, Warner does well not to flick across the line, shows the full face of the bat to defend the length ball right back
Warner and Mitchell Marsh are at the crease. Warner is on strike. Boult will open the attack
